Lunarpine was shocked at her response once again, Almost embarased by 
this display of emotion so close to his fellow Maximals. "Easy Wing, 
we might have won this battle but the tyrants still functioning." He 
couldn't yet put all the pieces together but he fealt an unremembered 
grudge toward Megatron. He dropped it for now, it was probably a 
grudge that aall the Maximals have against him. "If Megatron took off 
through the woods I'll find him, and when I do he's slag." 
Immediately the wolf remembered another score he had to settle. This 
one against the beast who cost him his major optics. (Ares)

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> ::Shadow Wing::
> 
> She flew down to Lunarpine. "Megatron has left.  He went off and 
> disappeared in the heavy forest.  I couldn't spot him after a 
while.  
> But he's gone for now."  She transformed into bot mode and hugged 
> Lunarpine. "One more battle won. Yeah for our side." She stood 
there 
> in front of him and smiled.  She really cared for this, gruff, 
tough, 
> sometimes harsh wolf that stood infront of her.  She discovered 
that 
> she just couldn't help but like him. Only, it was more 
than 'like'.  
> But she wasn't quite sure how much more than 'like' it was, but she 
> thought is was a whole lot more than 'like'.
